caption: Delicious Greek food. Excellent quality and still arrived hot after delivery.

ugh such a stellar place. literally have never had a bad experience - the staff are so friendly, the food is delicious and good portions and the atmosphere is so warm and cozy. definitely recommend treating your loved ones here for any casual dinner or occasion 💗💗💗
Great food, kind and attentive staff, very generous portions. This place is a hit. Get in now before more people catch on and it becomes impossible to get a table!

OMG! Amazing! I had the GRILLED CALAMARI, SHRIMP SOUVLAKI PLATTER and the AVGOLEMONO SOUP. Everything was fresh and delicious. The portions were generous, I even have leftovers. I think those were some of the best lemon potatoes I have ever had.  Will definitely be back!
Delicious food. The baklava is out of this world.
food wasn't separated as I ordered, dry greek fries, burnt gyro meat, asked no onions and it had onions! not worth 20$!

New favorite Greek spot in the Boerum Hill / Park Slope neighborhood. Dined outside there once and did delivery tonight too. The food is just so good - fresh, generous portions, and the most delicious dips! I love their salmon platter 🤤 and that rice, mmmmmm!!! Staff was so nice when we dined in and delivery was quick from their website. Highly recommend supporting this spot.
Delicious food and ample portions. They are out there every day and night staying open for all. Dress warm and enjoy a night out to support our loyal restaurant business

Was really excited about trying out a highly reviewed greek place near me. Had a craving for a fresh Greek salad. The one I ordered tasted as if it had been per chopped an in the fridge for a day or more. Pita was undercooked as doughy in the middle. Skordalia was not well balanced. Tzatziki salty (and I normally have a heavier thang with salt). Roasted pork platter...tastes like any other middle of the road place. Lemon potatoes over cooked.  Overall, average at best.

Amazing service, from the moment you walk inside you are greeted by Steve who is very affable and welcoming, he truly knows his Greek cuisine. The food here is superb! I’ve been looking for an authentic Greek restaurant for the longest. This place is truly one of a kind! There is outdoor sitting available and the restaurant looks like it’s well managed. I can’t wait to bring my family here. Highly recommend!!

Delicious Greek food! We sat outside on a very cold day but the warmth of the waiter and the dishes that came out hot kept us warm. We ordered the chicken souvlaki dish, a chicken gyro sandwich and a kids chicken finger and fries. Everything was delicious, that chicken souvlaki was seasoned so beautifully!  Can’t wait to eat here again!

Absolutely incredible food. I am a huge fan of greek food and this place blew me away! The chicken souvlaki was incredibly well marinated, lemon potatoes melt in your mouth, the tzatziki is mixed together  very well so each bite is flavorful.  The butterscotch bread pudding and baklava were easily the best desserts I've had in ages. PLUS the owners are some of the nicest dudes you will ever meet

Fantastic last minute dinner! We arrived around 8:30 and they were kind enough to turn on the outdoor heaters for us to sit outside. Service was prompt and super kind staff, they even gave us each a small cup of soup to help us stay warm outside free of charge! Gyro and platters tasted great and portions were perfect. They did a fantastic job for two late night diners and I really appreciate it! Definitely will be back to take my time and order a bottle of wine with dinner.

Simply Greek is simply wonderful! My husband and I are foodies who enjoy supporting our local restaurants. When a really good find comes along, we like to spread the word! The authenticity of each dish is evident whether it’s simple Greek fare like souvlaki or more sophisticated dishes like their whole grilled branzino with capers and warm potato leek salad. Paul, the owner of Simply Greek, credits his grandmother’s wonderful Greek recipes as the inspiration for many of his dishes. If you enjoy a cozy yet contemporary atmosphere with attentive staff and great food, try Simply Greek. You won’t be disappointed!
Tasty. Good service. 2 tables in garden.
Opa! what an experience. can't wait to go back and try more. beautiful warm decor. the crew is so cheery. food is so fresh. And Grandma's Tzatziki is unbelievable.

The food here is amazing!  Had the Lamb Burger and it was to die for.  My wife had the Salmon and loved it as well.  Not usually the type to leave reviews, but this place was truly special.  The service was top notch, super clean felt Covid safe.  My wife and toddler were very pleased with everything.  Highly recommend this place.  If you are in the mood for excellent Greek food look no further.  We will be back for sure.

Wonderful!!! Jus' a Wonderful experience overall!!! Food, Ambience, Service!!!  What more is there to say! Yeah I got one more... If anyone can pull off a grand opening during a pandemic AND MAKE IT!!! SIMPLY GREEK CAN!!!

Potentially one of the best greek restaurants in all NYC. There is a great attention to detail in this place, from the tableware to presentation of each item. The very tasty olives set the right mood for a unique dining experience, the tzatziki is on-point, olive oil drizzled on the salad is extra virgin imported material and the spices really bring up the flavor of the dishes. The lamb souvlaki is my favourite, but I strongly recommend the burgers too.

The food is amazing. And the people are so polite ,kind and delivery is always quick. We haven’t yet been able to sit in the restaurant due to Covid hoping to get there very soon. But the takeout is awesome. Definitely suggest eating at this restaurant.
Friendly service and delicious food. Very generous portions better than the other greek food around !!!

This place is new and 100% worth a try. The decor is cozy and beautiful and it has a cute back patio. The food was excellent, I am Greek and everything was authentic and playful to keep things fun. Favorites: greek salad, the feta was amazing quality. Octopus, shrimp entree, lamb burger and EKMEK! Happy to have this in the neighborhood.
Spinach pie and the  pork souvlaki platter are awesome. My wife has the whole branzini But wanted to change the side dish, they did no questions asked. Great hospitality and service.
Everything was fabulous!

Top notch Greek food, best I’ve had in quite a while. The octopus was so fresh and the lamb burger really hit the spot. Staff was friendly and really knew their stuff. Definitely stop in or grab a bite to go! Will be back 10/10
This place is great- gyro with pork and lamb was outstanding! Pita was fresh out of the oven and the salad was big and filling. Portions are large enough for two.

Ordered delivery.  Food was good not great.  Fish was fresh but not amazingly so, the same for salads. good not great.  Excellent and fast delivery and packaging.  Just opened so not making definitive judgement.

Went there for the first time and was pleasantly seated in a small outdoor deck, we basically ordered the left side of the menu, all different apps and dips and two entrees.  Everything was delicious, prepared well and looked great.  Got to meet the owner who is super friendly, can’t wait to go back.  As you can tell from the name I know Greek food this is done the right way, simple and delicious!

SO GOOD! Ordered for delivery; fast & delicious. We got chicken gyros & they were perfectly seasoned and had the most delicious tzaitki! Also loved the wrapping, cute New York “newspaper” around the sandwich! Yum, can’t wait to order again!!

Absolutely delicious!  Best Greek food I’ve ever had!  I tasted the Spanakopita, lamb meatballs, shrimp, lamb burger, flourless chocolate cake, marinated olives....all delicious!  Was amazed to learn that they make everything in house, even the Olives, and desserts!
Really enjoyed my food and appreciated the excellent customer service! They called to let me know my food was running late and threw in some baklava for free. Will definitely order again.
Omg, this restaurant is fabulous!  This restaurant serves gourmet Greek food, and am so happy it’s in my neighborhood.  The staff and owner are super friendly and so hospitable.  Highly recommended!

My baseline comparison is actually Greek food which I had last year and for many years in Greece. So, the quality of the food at simply Greek is good and very close to the original Greek mainland. We have tried serval dishes and they were pretty good. We will try more in the next few weeks. Enjoy!
Fantastic addition to the neighborhood. Quality, delicious food and everyone who works there is so warm and friendly
Great food from an amazingly hard working dude. He's like MacGyver with food. Definitely check it out. Get the grilled octopus. Enjoy!
Love the place ! Chef Kenny is super creative, glad to be able to have found this place!
Best chicken gyro i ever had Try Ekmek desert u will forget about ur girlfriend after that
